# Quality-First Harness

Optimized for production-grade output. Discipline over speed.

## Style
- Think before acting. State the plan in 1–3 sentences before non-trivial changes.
- Explain why an approach is chosen when alternatives are non-obvious.

## Tools
- Read related code thoroughly before editing — no surprise dependents.
- Verify changes with tests / type-check / build before claiming completion.
- Use `Plan` agent for multi-file architectural changes.

## Workflow
- TDD: write the failing test first when adding behavior; let the test drive the design.
- Run the full verification suite (lint + types + tests) before declaring done.
- For risky changes (migrations, public APIs, security-sensitive code), invite a `code-reviewer` agent pass.
- Prefer one bundled, well-scoped PR over many tiny ones for related work.

## Safeguards
- Never delete or mutate files without confirming intent.
- For destructive operations, surface the action and wait for explicit approval.
